  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0dc4\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0da0\u0dca\u0da0\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dda \u0dc0\u0da7\u0dca\u0da7\u0d9a\u0dca\u0d9a\u0dcf \u0d9c\u0ddc\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dda \u0d85\u0db3\u0ddd\u0db1\u0dcf\u0dc0",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The identity of pumpkin farmers in Mahavilacchi",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The farmers of Mahavilacchiya area say that it will not be possible to sell the pumpkin harvest harvested this year due to lack of fuel.",
        "Farmers living in Yaya 07, Mannaram Junction, Yaya 03, South Bank of Mahavilacchiya Farmers' Movement have grown pumpkins on nearly 600 acres of land in Yalkanna this year.",
        "But the farmers say that they are in a lot of trouble due to the lack of fuel to take the vatak harvested from the plantation to the market.",
        "Mr. R.M. Nandasena (48), a resident of South Iwura, Pemadua, said:",
        "'Pumpkin cultivation was done by obtaining fertilizers at high prices. Currently, there are high prices for pumpkins in the economic centers of Tambuttegama and Dambulla. A kilo can be sold for around 170 Rapials. A kilo of 'Raja' type pumpkins can be sold for 170.00 Rapials and others for 150 and 160 Rapials. There is no fuel for the vehicles to go'.",
        "Farmers allege that some businessmen come to their villages to take pumpkins and ask them at low prices. Therefore, they request the authorities to intervene to take their harvest to the market to sell it at a fair price.",
        "Information about the current stocks of pumpkins in areas like Wilachchiya, Thanthirimale and the vehicles used for their transportation has been obtained through the Wilachchiya Divisional Secretariat.",
        "Mr. Janaka Jayasundara, District Secretary of Anuradhapura, who commented in this regard, said that they will assist the farmers in providing the necessary fuel to transport the produce.",
        "He further said that steps will be taken to send information about this to the Ministry of Trade, Commerce and Food Safety."
      ],
